**/.next/
**/.worktrees/
**/node_modules/
**/out/
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
.claude/settings.local.json
# ENT-001 durable journal bucket split: coord/.runtime/ is ignored by default,
# but the DURABLE governance evidence buckets are un-ignored (tracked) so a
# fresh clone can validate its own board. Tracked: the journal and the canonical
# plan records. Everything else under .runtime/ (locks, sessions, agents.json,
# gate-procs, session-threads, the latest-snapshot pointer, scratch) stays
# ignored. Note: `coord/.runtime/*` (NOT `coord/.runtime/`) so git descends
# into the dir and the `!` negations below can re-include specific paths.
coord/.runtime/*
# Durable journal (tracked). The per-mutation governance-snapshots/ history
# bucket is intentionally NOT tracked (COORD-105): board validate never reads
# it, and tracking it caused unbounded git bloat (2427+ files / ~28MB, no
# pruning). COORD-108: governance-latest-snapshot.json is likewise NOT tracked —
# it is a single regenerable board-state-at-last-mutation pointer that MUTATES on
# every gov command (perpetually-dirty worktree) and is not needed for
# fresh-clone validate; the journal + plan records are the durable evidence. Both
# stay on local disk as recovery scratch.
!coord/.runtime/governance-events.ndjson
# Durable canonical plan records (tracked).
!coord/.runtime/plans/
coord/evidence/**/*.json
**/artifacts/gates/
# COORD-138: the bundled cockpit demo ships a curated, read-only gate-artifact
# fixture so `npm run demo` shows passing proofs on the Gates/Evidence views.
# These are committed demo data (not real gate output), so un-ignore them.
!examples/demo/*/artifacts/
!examples/demo/*/artifacts/gates/
!examples/demo/*/artifacts/gates/*.json
# COORD-140: coord/memory/ derived artifacts (decisions.ndjson etc.) are
# gitignored as DERIVED + REBUILDABLE (MEMORY_ARCHITECTURE.md §6.1). The precise
# rules live in coord/.gitignore (consulted for paths under coord/); this anchor
# documents the policy at the repo root.
coord/memory/decisions.ndjson
